Such a brilliant video.
Thank you so much.


Just a hint:

I got stuck around 2:48:00 with the following error.


"TypeError: Post.find is not a function"


So checking the web for mongoose samples I found that I have to use Schema (not SchemaType) to get the Schema actually created.

########
const postSchema = mongoose.Schema({
    title: String,
    body: String,
});

const Post = mongoose.model("Post", postSchema);
module.exports = Post;
########

Just in case someone finds that useful.

Guys if you see an issue of infinite response time, make sure to response properly i.e  return it as soon as the work is done

   return res.status(401).json({
      status: "failed",
      message: "unauthorized",
    });

